==电影附属动画短片中的描述==
The ''Rainbow Rocks'' [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks/Animated shorts|animated shorts]] partially depict the band's formation, with each member discovering and taking up what would be their instrument of choice.

In [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks/Animated shorts#Guitar Centered|Guitar Centered]], Rainbow Dash acquires a new electric guitar after a "shred off" against [[Trixie (EG)|Trixie Lulamoon]]. In [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks/Animated shorts#Hamstocalypse Now|Hamstocalypse Now]], Fluttershy discovers her talent for the tambourine when tending to a rambunctious group of hamsters. In [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks/Animated shorts#Pinkie on the One|Pinkie on the One]], Pinkie Pie discovers her talent for playing the drums when her friends seek an outlet for her boundless energy. In [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks/Animated shorts#Player Piano|Player Piano]], Rarity takes up the keytar as a more portable substitute for the grand piano. In [[My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Rainbow Rocks/Animated shorts#A Case for the Bass|A Case for the Bass]], Applejack recovers her bass guitar from [[Flim and Flam]] after [[Granny Smith]] accidentally sells it to them at a yard sale.

在《吉他争霸》中，[[人类云宝]]和[[人类崔克茜]]进行了一场“吉他对决”后，挑选了一把新的吉他。在《仓鼠时尚》中，人类小蝶在安抚一群闹哄哄的仓鼠时发现了自己在演奏铃鼓方面的天赋。在《萍琪时间》中，乐团的其他成员

